      "content": "Raising minimum wages in rural areas will likely force small businesses like yours to cut corners on essential services or reduce hours to stay profitable. You might see a drop in overall sales volume as customers become more price-sensitive, or you could be forced to raise prices on your goods, which hurts your local economy. The real cost isn't just the wage increase itself, but the potential loss of your competitive edge against larger chains that can absorb these costs more easily.",
